<subSubSection id="C34472A7FFFB6826459A34F1BB83FDD1" pageId="14" pageNumber="297" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFFB6826459A34F1BB83FDD1" blockId="14.[151,1436,289,604]" pageId="14" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFFB6826459A34F1BB40FD99" bold="true" box="[199,315,506,532]" pageId="14" pageNumber="297">Remarks.</emphasis>
This distinctive species was previously recorded from many sites in the NT, four sites in northern WA, and two sites (
<specimenCount id="9D58EAA5FFFB6826442C3715BB9DFDB4" box="[369,486,542,569]" pageId="14" pageNumber="297" type="male">two males</specimenCount>
) in northern 
<collectingRegion id="499AEFCEFFFB6826472B3715B881FDB5" box="[630,762,542,568]" country="Australia" name="Queensland" pageId="14" pageNumber="297">Queensland</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF5CDDFFFB682646553715B9BDFDB5" author="Cartwright, D. I." box="[776,966,542,568]" pageId="14" pageNumber="297" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref14543" refString="Cartwright, D. I. (1990) The Australian species of Ecnomus McLachlan (Trichoptera: Ecnomidae). Memoirs of the Museum of Victoria, 51, 1 - 48. https: // doi. org / 10.24199 / j / mmv. 1990.51.01" type="journal article" year="1990">Cartwright 1990</bibRefCitation>
). Here, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFFB682641403714BEA6FDB5" authorityName="Cartwright" authorityYear="1990" box="[1053,1245,543,568]" class="Insecta" family="Ecnomidae" genus="Ecnomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="297" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="veratus">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFFB682641403714BEA6FDB5" box="[1053,1245,543,568]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="297">Ecnomus veratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded from a further eleven sites in the NT.
</paragraph>
